The paper deals with the problem of estimating frequency moments of a data stream, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper specifically focuses on the class of algorithms based on linear sketches, which is a popular technique for solving this problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with the space complexity of the algorithms. The paper may also fall under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) as it discusses lower bounds. Additionally, the paper involves some aspects of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) as it deals with the problem of estimating moments. Finally, the paper may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as frequency moments are often used in analyzing network data.
